The skill should:

When to use – Use when the user wants to update, modify, or extend the frontend UI of the quantum-hybrid-portfolio project.

Project context – Explain:

React (Create React App) frontend in frontend/
Flask API at http://localhost:5000 (proxy in package.json)
Main entry: frontend/src/App.js → CustomizableQuantumDashboard.js
API: frontend/src/services/api.js (optimizePortfolio, backtest, market data, config endpoints)
Objectives supported after QSW migration: equal_weight, markowitz, min_variance, hrp, qubo_sa, vqe, hybrid, target_return
UI update guidelines:

Prefer keeping the API contract in api.js unchanged unless the backend changes
Do not use QSW-specific parameters (omega, evolution_time, evolution_method); the backend uses notebook methods
For objective selection, support the new objectives from /api/config/objectives
Use Recharts for charts and react-toastify for notifications
Common tasks – Include concise steps for:

Updating the objective dropdown to match new objectives
Adding K_screen/K_select inputs for the hybrid objective
Fixing ESLint warnings in CustomizableQuantumDashboard.js
Improving responsiveness or accessibility
File locations – Reference:

frontend/src/App.js, frontend/src/CustomizableQuantumDashboard.js
frontend/src/components/dashboard/ (RegimeComparison, BacktestPanel, ObjectiveSelector, etc.)
frontend/src/services/api.js
frontend/package.json (proxy: http://localhost:5000)
Verification – Run npm start in frontend/ and ensure the backend is running on port 5000 before testing UI changes.